Senior Business Intelligence & Analytics Engineer (SSAS) – USC Only 
 
The Senior Business Intelligence & Analytics Engineer position must have knowledge and wide-ranging experience with Microsoft SQL Analysis Services (SSAS) and Microsoft SQL Reporting Services (SSRS). This position is based in our St. Louis office.

A successful candidate will have experience with data warehousing and business intelligence systems.

This role is responsible for design and development of reports, dashboards and ad-hoc queries, and calls for someone who is comfortable working with clients as well as state and federal agencies to discover requirements, then formulate them into solutions.

We are looking for an individual with a positive, can-do attitude who can to adapt to a changing environment.

We are in the midst of building our next-generation product while undergoing an agile transformation. This will require critical thinking skills as it relates to software that is “emergent".



What you will do
• Design, build and maintain data marts and cubes using SSAS;
• Design and develop reports using MS SQL Reporting Services (SSRS);
• Deploy, maintain and generate reports from a data warehouse;
• Capable of gathering requirements from clients and agencies, understanding the user’s requirement and converting requirements into functional/technical specifications and developing a strategy for designing and building Business Intelligence solutions;
• Create business intelligence tools or systems, including design of related databases, spreadsheets, or outputs;
• Publish and integrate reports into Microsoft SharePoint;
• Conduct or coordinate tests to ensure intelligence is consistent with defined needs;
• Create or review technical design documentation to ensure the accurate development of reporting solutions;
• Maintain library of model documents, templates or other reusable knowledge assets;
• Provide technical support for existing reports, dashboards or other tools;
• Create working prototypes for our sales team to use as demonstrations for potential clients;


We ask
• Excellent oral and written communication skills;
• Excellent technical acumen and ability to learn quickly;
• Enthusiastic and fun individual with an attitude of team empowerment;
• 3+ years of combined experience in data warehousing/business intelligence/analytics and reporting systems;
• 3+ years’ experience with MS SQL Analysis Services (SSAS);
• 3+ years’ experience developing reports in MS SQL Server Reporting Services (SSRS) & Visual Studio;
• 1+ year of MS SharePoint experience;
• 1+ year of experience with MS SQL Integration Services (SSIS);
• 1+ year of ETL scripting experience;
• Experience with data warehouse creation desirable, but not required;
• Experience with Crystal Reports and have the ability to interact and analyze existing reports;
• Knowledge of MS SQL Profiler, query execution plans and SQL tuning techniques;
• Experience building and executing sufficient tests of developed solutions;
• Preferred candidate will have basic programming experience and working knowledge of software development tools including: VB.Net, Visual Basic 6, ASP, C#, Power Pivot, Visual Studio;
• Bachelor’s Degree in computer science or equivalent;
• This position will be based in our St. Louis, MO office.


Your approach
• Flexibility and the ability to work in a continually changing, client-focused environment;
• Ability to balance multiple high-priority deliverables;
• Strong analytical skills;
• Strong oral, written and interpersonal communications skills;
• Self-managed and motivated;
• Ability to work effectively both independently and in a team environment;
• Ability to follow through tasks to completion;
• Very organized and detail oriented;
• Customer-friendly attitude.

Inovalon is a leading technology company that combines advanced cloud-based data analytics and data-driven intervention platforms to achieve meaningful insight and impact in clinical and quality outcomes, utilization, and financial performance across the healthcare landscape. Inovalon's unique achievement of value is delivered through the effective progression of Turning Data into Insight, and Insight into Action.

The Senior BI Analyst will be focused on building Visualization and Dashboards supporting the continuous evolution of Inovalon Business Intelligence platform, INDICES. In addition to building the dashboards, the Sr. BI Analyst will collaborate with IT for data and Product for subject-matter-expertise.

Develop visualization and dashboards leveraging Tableau and other such data visualization tools to provide clients insight into the data and analytics results;
Perform data aggregation to implement business rules and algorithms necessary to support data visualization;
Develop and maintain domain knowledge of relevant Inovalon products, and data sources related to product analytics and intervention;
Apply deep knowledge and strong intuition for client and product visualization needs by engaging in and supporting internal and external focus groups, client demos and other leadership interactions;
Work closely and support Product Development and IT organizations by providing relevant requirements from the visualization and data stand-point; and
Provide analytical support leadership in development and continuous refinement of visualization roadmap, and support requirement and change management processes.




Bachelor's degree or equivalent work experience required, Masters Degree, preferred;

5+ years of general work experience in one or more of the following areas: Business Intelligence, Reporting, Data Analysis, Data Management, or Technology required;
2+ years of data visualization or UI experience required;
Demonstrated proficiency of SQL skills required;
Highly creative mindset for problem solving and data visualization;
Strong balance between business and technology skills;
Ability to work under minimal supervision and execute complex projects;
Effective verbal, interpersonal and written communication skills verbal, and written communication;
Meticulous organizational skills;

Prior work experience using Tableau, especially with AtScale or Jethro; and

Healthcare (Payer or Pharma) industry experience.


Inovalon provides equal employment opportunities (EEO) to all employees and applicants for employment. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, or protected veteran status and will not be discriminated against on the basis of disability. 
 Apply Here PI101975710

